==2010 award winners== {{see also|2010 Southeast Emmy Awards winners}} The 2010 Southeast Emmy Awards were held on June 26, 2010 and broadcast live from [[Atlanta, Georgia]]. The event was held at the Grand Hyatt Buckhead and was hosted by television star [[Mike Pniewski]].<ref name="urlwww.natassoutheast.tv">{{cite web |url=http://www.natassoutheast.tv/docs/winners/Emmy2010Winners.pdf |title=www.natassoutheast.tv |author= [[NATAS]] |authorlink= |coauthors= |date= |format= |work= |publisher= |pages= |language= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |quote= |accessdate=2010-06-29}}2010 Emmy Award Winners</ref>
==2011 award winners== {{see also|2011 Southeast Emmy Award winners}} The 2011 Southeast Emmy Awards were held on June 18, 2011 and broadcasted live from [[Atlanta, Georgia]]. The event was held at the Grand Hyatt Buckhead and was hosted by Broadway producer [[Kenny Leon]].<ref name="2011 Emmy Awards">{{cite web|last=Leon|first=Kenny|title=Southeast Emmy Award Host|url=http://www.natassoutheast.tv/awards/2011emmys.html|work=Southeast Emmy Awards|publisher=NATAS|accessdate=27 June 2011}}</ref>
